com.googlecode.objectify
Class Key<T>

java.lang.Object
  com.googlecode.objectify.Key<T>
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<Key<?>>
public class Key<T>
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<Key<?>>

This is a typesafe version of the Key object. It is also Serializable and GWT-safe, enabling your entity objects to be used for GWT RPC should you so desire.

You may use normal Key objects as relationships in your entities if you desire neither type safety nor GWTability.

Author:
Jeff Schnitzer , Scott Hernandez

Field Detail

kindClassName

protected java.lang.String kindClassName
The name of the class which represents the kind. As much as we'd like to use the normal String kind value here, translating back to a Class for getKind() would then require a link to the OFactory, making this object non-serializable.
